body:
Quick C# Console app I put together to dump incoming args and environment.  After launching environment/args it launches pwsh which works as expected.  It's only when pwsh is the direct shell that I get the error.

One interesting note, this only happens if I install powershell using dpkg/apt.  If I use dotnet to install powershell as a global tool then use that global tool as my shell, I do not have this issue.  `dotnet tool install -g powershell`.  I've also included below how I've installed powershell and dotnet in WSL...

I'm going to try and compile powershell to see if I can debug a bit more.  

C# Console App/Shell
```c#
var rawArgs = Environment.GetCommandLineArgs();

Console.WriteLine("ARGS: {0}\r\nRAW ARGS: {1}", 
    String.Join(", ", args.Select(a => $"'{a}'")),
    String.Join(", ", rawArgs.Select(ra => $"'{ra}'")));

var rawEnvironmentVariables = Environment.GetEnvironmentVariables();
var environmentVariables = rawEnvironmentVariables.Keys.Cast<string>()
    .ToDictionary(k => k, 
                  k => (string)rawEnvironmentVariables[k]);
var environmentText = String.Join("\r\n", environmentVariables.OrderBy(ev => ev.Key)
    .Select(ev => $"\t{ev.Key}={ev.Value}"));

Console.WriteLine("ENVIRONMENT:\r\n{0}", environmentText);
Thread.Sleep(3000);
try
{
    Console.WriteLine("LAUNCHING POWERSHELL");
    var process = Process.Start("pwsh");
    process.WaitForExit();
    Console.WriteLine("FINISHED");
}
catch(Exception ex)
{
    Console.WriteLine("ERROR:\r\n{0}", ex);
    Thread.Sleep(3000);
}
finally
{
    Thread.Sleep(10000);
}
```

