Fresh Ubuntu install from Microsoft Store then:

```pwsh
wget https://packages.microsoft.com/config/ubuntu/20.04/packages-microsoft-prod.deb -O packages-microsoft-prod.deb;
sudo dpkg -i ./packages-microsoft-prod.deb;
sudo apt-get update; sudo apt-get install -y apt-transport-https curl;
sudo apt-get install -y dotnet-sdk-6.0 aspnetcore-runtime-5.0 git git-lfs vim make gcc g++ powershell;
```

Then edit `/etc/shells` to add `/usr/bin/pwsh.`  I've tested setting my shell to both `/usr/bin/pwsh` and `/opt/microsoft/powershell/7/pwsh` but both throw the error mentioned above.
